      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The maiden stayers kick us off. DROVE ALL NIGHT (3) put in a career-best performance when third over 1890m at Toowoomba last time out. Best figures measure up. Gets 2kg weight relief with the claim and is sure to run well. ALKEBULAN (6) has hit the top-four in three of her past four starts and looks to be working up to a maiden victory. Has to be included in calculations. RAINBOW GLITTER (10) got a long way back when 6 lengths from the winner in ninth over 1800m at Gold Coast last start, a less impressive effort than her fifth there the run before. This doesn't look as hard so she is set to turn things around. IT'S OK (7) finished 11th at her last appearance over 1800m at Gold Coast on June 6 after she gave away a big start. Well placed on this occasion and gets her chance to break the ice. Something for the Multiples: I DROVE ALL NIGHT (3)",
